OL,3,C'Incremental change won't cut it':
OL,4,CStarmer to give speech in fight to
OL,5,Ckeep job
OL,7,FThe prime minister faces a leadership
OL,8,Fchallenge by backbencher Catherine
OL,9,FWest as early as Monday if his Cabinet
OL,10,Fdoes not force him out, but he has
OL,11,Fvowed to stay on and see through what
OL,12,Fhe calls his "10-year project" for the
OL,13,FUK.
OL,15,FIn a speech on Monday, the PM is
OL,16,Fexpected to set out the next steps in
OL,17,Fhis plan to "build a stronger and
OL,18,Ffairer Britain", ahead of the King's
OL,19,FSpeech, which will set out his
OL,20,Fgovernment's priorities for new laws
OL,21,Fin Parliament.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1778508672
OL,3,C'Incremental change won't cut it':
OL,4,CStarmer to give speech in fight to
OL,5,Ckeep job
OL,7,F"To meet the challenges that our
OL,8,Fcountry faces incremental change won't
OL,9,Fcut it," he is expected to say. "On
OL,10,Fgrowth, defence, Europe, energy ` we
OL,11,Fneed a bigger response than we
OL,12,Fanticipated in 2024 because these are
OL,13,Fnot ordinary times.
OL,15,F"Strength through fairness. It's a
OL,16,Fcore Labour argument. And you will see
OL,17,Fthose values writ large in the King's
OL,18,FSpeech. And you will see hope, urgency
OL,19,Fand exactly whose side we are on."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@HO]qD@aOUwD@AOU{D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
